text: Diarmuid Wilson (born 20 November 1965) is an Irish Fianna Fáil politician who has served as a Senator for the Administrative Panel since September 2002. A member of Cavan County Council from 1999 to 2004, he was first elected to the Seanad in 2002 and was re-elected in 2007 and 2011. He is the nephew of John Wilson, who was a Teachta Dála, cabinet minister and Tánaiste. He is the Fianna Fáil whip in the Seanad and spokesperson for Labour Affairs, Trade and Commerce. ==See also== *Families in the Oireachtas ==References== ==External links== *Diarmuid Wilson's page on the Fianna Fáil website Category:1965 births Category:Living people Category:Alumni of St Patrick's College, Maynooth Category:Alumni of Brunel University London Category:Fianna Fáil senators Category:Local councillors in County Cavan Category:Members of the 22nd Seanad Category:Members of the 23rd Seanad Category:Members of the 24th Seanad Category:Members of the 25th Seanad Category:Members of the 26th Seanad
